                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310512-117-off687 t18310512-117-crimeloc689"></join>. I took the prisoner into my temporary service after the last Session, having known his father, who had worked for me - on the <rs id="t18310512-117-cd690" type="crimeDate">15th of April</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310512-117-off687 t18310512-117-cd690"></join> I sent him out with goods amounting to 1l. 18s. 4d.; he was to bring back the money, but I did not see him again till I met him on the Sunday afternoon, on Clerkenwell-green - I asked what he had done with the money; he at first said he had lost it, then that he had spent it in going to the theatre, and playing at pitch with some boys, who lived in the neighbourhood, on Saffron-hill.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310512-117-person911">
                  MARY 
                  ANN CAYLEY
               <interp inst="t18310512-117-person911" type="surname" value="ANN CAYLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310512-117-person911" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
